4.a)
   *fork()–creates a new child process by duplicating the parent process.
   *exec()–replaces the child process with another program and starts its execution.
  b)
   *wait() suspends the parent process until the child process completes its execution.
   *This confirmed proper synchronization and prevents zombie processes.

  c)//psedo code
   START
   Create child process using fork()
   IF Child Process THEN
    Execute another program using exec()
   ELSE
    Wait for child process using wait()
    Display "Parent Process Resumed"
   END

